# Cyberland — Sprite atlas authoring

Canonical reference mod: **`mods/Cyberland.Demo.SpriteGallery`** (rows A–H matrix).

## Manifest schema (`*.atlas.json`)

| Section | Purpose |
|---------|---------|
| `pages[]` | PNG paths per atlas page (`path` relative to mod `Content/`) |
| `regions[]` | Named rects: `pixelRect`, optional `pivot`, `sizeWorld`, `nineSlice` |
| `animations` | Frame-list clips: `regionNames`, `secondsPerFrame`, `loop` |
| `sheets` | Uniform grid clips: `regionName`, `columns`, `frameCount`, timing |
| `nineSlice` | UI-only insets on a region (used by retained HUD `image` nodes) |

Hand-edit `animations`, `sheets`, and `nineSlice` after running **`scripts/Generate-SpriteAtlases.ps1`** (baker emits regions/pages only).

## Locale overlays

- Overlay manifest: `Content/Locale/{culture}/Textures/Atlases/{same relative path as base}`.
- Overlay page PNGs: same folder tree under `Locale/{culture}/` (e.g. `Locale/de/Textures/Atlases/gallery.page0.png`).
- Scene bindings always use **canonical** paths (`Textures/Atlases/gallery.atlas.json`); the catalog resolves culture at load time.

## Binding precedence (`SpriteAtlasBinding`)

1. `sheet` clip name (if set)
2. else `animation` clip name
3. else static `region` name

Set **`localeInvariant: true`** to skip locale overlays and load the base manifest only (row E in SpriteGallery).

## When to use which component

| Need | Component |
|------|-----------|
| Atlas region / animation / sheet | `sprite-atlas-binding` |
| Standalone PNG (VFS path, locale folder override) | `sprite-localized-asset` |

Engine systems (mod does not register): **`SpriteAtlasAnimationSystem`** (early parallel), **`SpriteAtlasBindingSystem`** + **`SpriteLocalizedAssetSystem`** (late serial), **`SpriteRenderSystem`**.

## UI `sourceTexture`

- `manifest.json#region` — resolves via **`TextureSourceResolver`**; `nineSlice` comes from manifest unless JSON overrides (prefer manifest-only).
- Builtins: `white`, `missing`, `defaultNormal`.

## Performance

Preload atlases in **`Mod.OnLoadAsync`** via **`context.LoadSpriteAtlas(...)`** so the first frame avoids catalog miss + GPU upload on the render path.

## Release assets

Large PNGs ship via per-mod **`content.release.manifest.json`** + **`scripts/Sync-CyberlandAssets.ps1`**, not git. See SpriteGallery README for **`Package-SpriteGallery-Assets.ps1`**.

